\f0\b \cf5 \strokec5 26 
\f1\b0 In the sixth month of Elizabeth\'92s pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a town in Galilee, 
\f0\b 27 
\f1\b0 to a virgin pledged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. The virgin\'92s name was Mary. 
\f0\b 28 
\f1\b0 The angel went to her and said, \'93Greetings, you who are highly favored! The Lord is with you.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf5 \strokec5 29 
\f1\b0 Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be. 
\f0\b 30 
\f1\b0 But the angel said to her, \'93Do not be afraid, Mary; you have found favor with God.\cf2 \strokec2  \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
